demonstration_site_details: In Wolaita one of the SCLAMP-EA project implementation areas, Send a Cow supported a total of 312 farmers to establish Push Pull Learning sites. Each of the farmers established the push pull learning sites on an average land size of 400m2 of of land. In total, a total of 12.5 hectares of land was covered by a push pull learning sites in Wolaita zone alone. These learning sites will be used as a center of skill transfer on CSPM.

In Dawro, one of the SCLAMP-EA project implementation areas, Send a Cow supported a total of 162 farmers to establish Push Pull Learning sites. Each of the farmers established the push pull learning sites on an average land size of 400m2 of of land. In total, a total of 6.5 hectares of land was covered by a push pull learning sites in Dawro zone alone. These learning sites will be used as a center of skill transfer on CSPM.

details_of_activity: SCLAMP EA project, through facilitation of Send a Cow Ethiopia distributed IPM starter kits for a total of 162 farmers in Dawro zone. In the month of April, 2021, each farmer received 1kg of maize,100 gram of desmodium and 423 splits of Brachiaria grass. All the 162 farmers established push pull plots on their own farm which will be used as a learning sites for themselves and other farmers.

In the month of April and May, 2021, SACE trained a total of 77 government agricultural extension staff on the concept and practical implementation of Climate Smart Pest Management approaches. The participants were drawn from Wolaita and Dawro. Following the training, the trained agricultural extension workers are supporting the transfer of the skill to farmers in their respective areas.

In March and April, 2021, Send a Cow trained a total 281 cluster level associations members as a trainers of  farmers on climate smart pest management approaches. out of the total trained CLA members, 129 are in Dawro and 152 are in Wolaita. These trained CLA member have already started rolling out the skills they acquired for other farmers i  their neighborhoods.

in the month of April, 20221, SCLAMP-EA project distributed IPM starter kits for a total of 312 farmers in Wolaita. Each farmer got 1.2kg of maize, 100 gram of green leaf desmodium and 423 splits of Brachiaria grass.

Until April, 2021, a total of 7 Push Pull Demonstration plots have been established in 5 woredas/districts in Dawro as part of the strengthening the Farmer Training Centers which are serving as Farm Field Schools. The 7 Push pull demo plots established in Dawro cover an area of 7000m2 of land.

Until April, 2021, a total of 7 Push Pull Demonstration plots have been established in 5 woredas/districts in Wolaita as part of the strengthening the Farmer Training Centers which are serving as Farm Field Schools. The 7 Push pull demo plots established in Wolaita cover an area of 7225m2 of land.

details_of_activity: Training of lead farmers on group dynamics and gender. The main objective of the training was to enable lead farmers to acquire basic skills in leadership and management of the group and also to enable them to appreciate the benefits of being in a group. They were then tasked to go back to their groups and train their group members on what they had been trained upon

details_of_activity: Trainer of trainees from Namutumba and Mbale were trained in Mbale by Dr. Girma Hailu from ICIPE. This training was on the management of cereal stem borers, leaf miners, fall army worm, striga and tuta absolute. This training also focused on push pull technology. The training involved both theoretical and practical sessions. The objective of this training was to train the trainer of trainees so that they would go back and Cascade the information received to the respective lead farmers in Namutumba and Mbale districts respectively. The gender breakdown am providing on the next page is for Namutumba.

details_of_activity: In the month of November, 2020, a total of 12 (all male) staff of Send a Cow Ethiopia visited push pull plots established by ICIPE Ethiopia in Sidama regional state in southern Ethiopia. During this visit, Send a Cow Ethiopia's field level staff learned how farmers in the visited area are controlling the problem of stemborer pest through the application of push pull technology.

details_of_groups: Up to the end of December, 2020, Send a Cow Ethiopia created and strengthen a total of 265 self help groups of farmers in Wolaita and Dawro Each of the 265 farmer groups have an average of 20 members with a total members of 5300 farmers (3710 of them are female). Of the total groups, 145 are in Wlolaita and 120 are in Dawro.

details_of_activity: From December, 2020 up to January, 2021, Send a Cow Ethiopia trained a total of 32 agricultural extension workers drawn from Wolaita and Dawro on the concept and practical implementation of Climate Smart Pest Management Approaches. Out of the 32 extension workers 12 are from Send a Cow Ethiopia's projects while the remaining 20 are from local government agriculture offices.

Starting from the start of the project up to the end of January 31, 2021, a total 712 (282 female) Peer Farmer Trainers /PFTs/ were trained by SACE as Trainlines of Trainers of SCLAMP EA project Of the 712 training of trainers participants, 472 of them are in Wolaita while 240 of them are in Dawro.
